CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
MOVABLE FEAST: TAKE-HOME HOLIDAY FARE; 
</P>
<P>
CHUTNEYS FROM SRI LANKA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Barbara Hansen 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
THE CHUTNEYS AND CHILI SAUCES on sale at the Siri Lanka Curry House in 
Hollywood really spice up a meal. 
</P>
<P>
Among the great Sri Lankan food discoveries available there are mango and apple 
chutney -- both sweet and hot. Apples don't grow in Sri Lanka, a tropical 
island located just off the southern tip of India, but co-owner Kusala 
Siriwardhane needed an alternative for the seasonal mango. 
</P>
<P>
The chutneys are priced at $5.95 each; chili sauces, $4.95. Packed in 
eight-ounce jars, they make ideal gifts for people with exotic tastes. 
</P>
<P>
 Siri Lanka Curry House, 1308 N. Highland Ave., Hollywood; (213) 
466-8238.Barbara Hansen 
</P>
</TEXT>
