<HEADLINE>
<P>
PORTRAIT OF A PLANET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Did everyone marvel at those stunning photos of clear-cut forests in "Portrait 
of a Planet" (Nov. 11)? I would be very surprised if the ongoing devastation in 
Northern California has nothing to do with the decrease in rainfall in Southern 
California since World War II. For what it's worth, I'm planting trees in my 
own yard, and I'll give them all the water they need, Bradley's 
10%-water-reduction decree be damned. If Central Valley farmers can throw away 
their cheap water running sprinklers in the noonday sun on surplus crops like 
cotton and alfalfa, I can take all the 15-minute showers I please. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM LEIDENTHAL 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
