<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding "My Aching Back," by Michael S. Wilkes MD and Miriam Schuchman MD 
(Nov. 11): A point missed by the doctors was the mention of physical therapy 
for treatment of back injuries. Granted, there are good therapists and 
not-so-good therapists; however, care and education offered by physical 
therapists can be invaluable to the individual suffering back pain. With the 
use of ice, heat, ultrasound, electrical stimulation, stretching and 
strengthening exercises and general conditioning, back problems can be 
successfully rehabilitated and reinjury prevented. 
</P>
<P>
VICTORIA G. MOSSE-DEWITT 
</P>
<P>
West Hills 
