BUS TRIP IS PLANNED TO ROSE BOWL PARADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Manhattan Beach Recreation Department is sponsoring a bus trip to the Rose 
Parade in Pasadena on New Year's Day. 
</P>
<P>
Participants will have reserved grandstand seats on Colorado Boulevard for 
close-up viewing of the parade and a box lunch. The cost is $48 for residents 
($47 with senior discount card), $61 for non-residents. The reservation 
deadline is Thursday. The bus will depart Joslyn Center at 6 a.m. Jan. 1 and 
Manhattan Heights at 6:15 a.m. and will return at 1 p.m. and 12:45 p.m. For 
more information, call 545-5621, Ext. 321. 
