<P>
MAN IS SHOT TO DEATH WHILE VISITING FAMILY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Los Angeles man who police say may have become caught up in an ongoing 
argument while visiting relatives was shot to death Friday in Inglewood. 
</P>
<P>
Eugene Lambert Jr., 63, was pronounced dead at Daniel Freeman Memorial Hospital 
in Inglewood after the 5:18 p.m. shooting in the 3300 block of West 85th 
Street, Sgt. Ed Eccles said. 
</P>
<P>
No arrests have been made, and the shooting remains under investigation, Eccles 
said. Police declined to release further information. 
</P>
