capsizing of a ferry returning them to the carrier Saratoga off Haifa, Israel. 
Investigators searched for clues as to why the chartered ferry capsized in 
choppy seas early Saturday. Survivors said the ferry went under almost 
instantly after it was swamped while ferrying about 100 crew members to the 
aircraft carrier from shore leave in Haifa. Right, a sailor waits at the docks. 
Reuters; Photo, A U.S. seaman, wrapped in a blanket, waits for transportation 
back to carrier Saratoga in Haifa after 19 sailors died in ferry capsizing. 
