<P>
FLYING LESSON ENDS IN CRASH-LANDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A flight instructor and student who mistakenly thought their wheels were down 
crash-landed at John Wayne Airport Saturday on their third practice landing of 
the day, county firefighters reported. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured. Capt. Dan Young, a Fire Department spokesman, said the 
single-engine Cherokee Arrow slid across the 19 Left Runway about noon after 
making two successful touch-and-go maneuvers. Its propeller was bent and the 
underside of the fuselage was damaged. Aboard were instructor Leslie Glatt, 45, 
of Redondo Beach, and his student, Charles Kelly, 42, of Costa Mesa. They are 
members of the JG 52 Flying Club. 
