<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 YOUTHS BADLY INJURED WHEN STRUCK BY CARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Ventura County children were seriously injured Saturday when they were hit 
by cars in separate accidents. 
</P>
<P>
An 8-year-old Oxnard boy was hit Saturday afternoon as he ran into the street 
at Del Sol Park, Oxnard police said. 
</P>
<P>
At 12:26 p.m., Hugo Alcala ran into traffic near the intersection of Rose 
Avenue and San Gorgonio Street and hit the side of a moving vehicle driven by 
Margaret Trevino, 29, also of Oxnard, police said. Hugo was taken to Ventura 
County Medical Center and admitted to intensive care, where he was reported in 
guarded condition Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Trevino was cited by officers for driving without a license, police said. An 
investigation is continuing. 
</P>
<P>
At about 2 p.m. in the 300 block of North Ojai Road, 17-year-old Cecilia 
Rodriquez was struck by a car driven by her father, Eduviges Rodriquez, and 
knocked through a block fence, Santa Paula police said. Cecilia was taken to 
Santa Paula Memorial Hospital and then was transferred to Ventura County 
Medical Center, where she underwent surgery. 
</P>
<P>
No arrests were made, and the investigation is continuing, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
