<HEADLINE>
<P>
E. WASHINGTON HALTS USD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHENEY, Wash. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hank Egan is stuck on 99. 
</P>
<P>
With a 73-69 loss to Eastern Washington Saturday night on Reese Court, the 
University of San Diego men's basketball team once again failed to earn Egan 
his 100th career victory. 
</P>
<P>
It was the Toreros' (5-4) fourth consecutive loss -- all on the road -- after 
they opened the season 4-0, while Eastern Washington (4-5) broke a four-game 
losing streak of its own. 
</P>
<P>
"We got a good effort," said Egan, "the road is just starting to beat us down." 
</P>
<P>
Although down 42-33 at the half, USD made a run in the end, cutting Eastern 
Washington's lead to two twice. 
</P>
<P>
Down 65-56 with 6:41 to go, USD ran off seven consecutive points to cut the 
Eagles lead to 65-63 with 3:33 left. In that run, Wayman Strickland had a free 
throw, Dondi Bell scored from the inside, Michael Brown made two free throws 
and Kelvin Woods had a rebound layup. 
</P>
<P>
USD committed 20 turnovers to Eastern Washington's nine, and shot 40% (22 of 
55) from the field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
