<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MOORPARK WOMEN RUN WINNING STREAK TO 14 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Moorpark College women's basketball team defeated Orange Coast, 99-73, in a 
nonconference game at Moorpark on Saturday night, the Raiders' school-record 
14th consecutive win. The previous mark was set during the 1986-87 season. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark (14-1) is undefeated since losing its first game to defending state 
champion Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
"It was a really good win," Moorpark Coach Gary Abraham said. "The girls had 
the record on their mind and wanted to break it." 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore Kerrie Marshall scored a game-high 28 points, including 16 in the 
first half, to help Moorpark, ranked fourth in the state, to a 17-point 
halftime advantage. 
</P>
<P>
Four other Moorpark players scored in double figures: Amy Chandler (21), Lisa 
Huffaker (14), Jeny Shotliff (10) and Donna Houck (12). 
</P>
<P>
The Raiders defeated Orange Coast (9-7) by three points earlier in the season 
in the championship game of the Cypress tournament. 
</P>
<P>
MEN 
</P>
<P>
Cerritos 83, Canyons 67 (OT) -- After deadlocks at the end of the first half 
and at the end of regulation, Cerritos (9-2) scored 19 consecutive points in 
the overtime period to win going away. 
</P>
