<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: PELLER TO HEAD ROCKWELL DEFENSE CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John B. Peller has been appointed president and center director of Rockwell 
International Corp.'s Strategic Defense Center in Seal Beach. 
</P>
<P>
He also will serve as a member of the corporation's senior management council. 
</P>
<P>
Peller, who joined Rockwell in 1961, was most recently vice president and 
associate center director. 
</P>
<P>
He succeeds George W. Jeffs, who will retire March 31 after more than 43 years 
with the company. 
</P>
<P>
