SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: BALDWIN PARK; 
</P>
<P>
FEE COLLECTION TRANSFERRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city has reversed its three-year policy of collecting "school impact" fees 
from developers, voting to transfer the collection responsibility to the 
Baldwin Park Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council voted 3 to 2 last week in favor of the school district 
collecting fees levied on developers for future school construction that may be 
necessitated by their projects. 
</P>
