<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SOUTH PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
ARCHITECT TO STUDY HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A private architect will be hired to make the final decision on a proposed 
three-story, 1,750-square-foot addition to the Oaklawn District estate of Lee 
Prentiss, a former mayor of South Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
The council agreed Wednesday that it lacked the expertise to judge whether 
Prentiss' building plans violate state guidelines on the alteration of 
historical buildings. 
</P>
<P>
In a 5-0 vote, the council ordered that an architect with historical expertise 
be hired at Prentiss' expense to oversee the design plans and give any final 
approval. The council set a 30-day limit on the process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
