<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: AZUSA; 
</P>
<P>
POLICE START BICYCLE PATROL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A two-officer bicycle patrol started full-time operation last week in shopping 
areas, apartment complexes and business districts. 
</P>
<P>
The two patrol officers -- wearing tennis shoes, riding pants and 
water-resistant jacket -- showed off their new bikes during a City Council 
meeting Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Police Chief Byron Nelson said Azusa is one of 40 U.S. cities with bicycle 
patrols. 
</P>
<P>
The program is not "just an amusing novelty" Nelson told the council. "It will 
be a powerful tool in preventing crime." 
</P>
